<td colspan=3 class=black><br><p><font class=b>How to play</font><br>
The object of the game is to remove cubes from the board as fast as possible by making "chains" of three or more adjacent cubes of the same color. Remember diagonals don't count! "Cubes to Go" marks your target number. Try to remove this cube.<br><br>
- Star Cubes are special and score bonus points. They also give a big penalty if you do not remove them from the board!<br>
- You can push a cube if the square behind is unoccupied. Push these cubes together to make chains.<br>
- When you get a chain that sets off another chain, you have a cubis! You get extra points for creating a cubis!<br>
- Stone blocks cannot be moved and will not fall. They may block your path or help you build stacks.<br>
- Cracked cubes will crumble away when hit but can also help you make a chain. Cubes may crack in a fall.<br>
- Wedges will raise a cube up. You cannot push with a wedge. Cubes stack up to 3 high.<br><br>







